2017 Fall AD Honor Roll 2021: Indoor – Competed in five meets … Finished as the runner-up in the long jump at the Shocker Prelude … Ran a season-best time in the 60-meter hurdles at the Herm Wilson Invitational with a time of 9.03 … Competed in the 60-meter hurdles and long jump at the Championship at The Peak … Jumped her season’s best mark in the long jump with a mark of 5.26m/17-3.25 at the Championship at The Peak. Outdoor – Ran in the 100-meter hurdles and 400-meter hurdles at five meets … Earned victories in the 100-meter hurdles at the Wichita State Open and the Shocker Open … Ran a season-best time of 14.46 in the 100-meter hurdles at the Rock Chalk Classic … Had a season-best performance in the 400-meter hurdles at the at the John McDonnell Invitational with a time of 1:03.22.

2020: Indoor - Competed at six meets in three different events … Earned a trio of third-place finishes at the Air Force Team Challenge (60-meter hurdles prelims, 60-meter hurdles final and long jump) … Jumped a season-best mark of 5.61m/18-5 in the long jump at the Gorilla Classic … Ran the 400 meters at the Triangular and Jayhawk Classic … Ran a personal-best time in the 60-meter hurdles at the AAC Championships with a time of 8.89 … Also competed in the long jump at the AAC Championships. Outdoor - 2020 season canceled.

2019: Indoor - Competed in 16 events in six meets...Opened the season at the Hawkeye Invitational finishing 13th in the long jump with a mark of 4.98m/16-4.25...Recorded a third place finish in the 60m hurdles (9.21) at the Shocker Prelude...Set a personal best long jump mark of 5.40m/17-8.75 at the Fourth Annual Gorilla Classic on Feb. 9...Ran a personal best 60m hurdles time of 9.07 at the Arkansas Qualifier on Feb. 15....Competed in two events at the American Athletic Conference Championships, finished 16th in the 60m hurdles (9.15) and 22nd in the long jump (5.15m/16-10.75). Outdoor - Ran in eight meets, finishing top-3 eight times...Opened the season with two top-5 finishes at the Herm Wilson Invitational, third in the 100m hurdles (15.16) and fourth in 400m hurdles (1:04.66)...Was part of the 4x400m team that won the Texas State Bobcat Invitational in 3:51.64, also placed 10th in the 400m hurdles (1:03.96)...Ran the second fastest preliminary time of 1:02.35 at the 92nd Kansas Relays, finished sixth in the finals clocking in at 1:02.83...Placed second in the Shocker Open 400m hurdles in 1:00.48...Ran 1:01.42 in the prelims at the American Athletic Conference Championships, finished fourth in the finals with a personal best time of 1:00.31.

2018: Indoor/Outdoor - Redshirted and competed unattached...Finished sixth in the long jump (4.79m/15-8.75) and seventh in the 400m (1:02.87) at the KSU/KU/WSU Triangular.

High School: Lettered four years in track and field, two years in volleyball and one year in basketball...School record holder in 100m hurdles, 400m hurdles, 55m hurdles, long jump and 4x400m relay team...Was section champion in the 400m hurdles and long jump...Member of National Honor Society...Personal best- 18-7.5 in the long jump, 14.98 in the 100m hurdles, 62.8 in the 400m hurdles, 8.81 in the 55m hurdles.

Personal: Daughter of Kristine McCormick...Has a brother, Christian...Brother played football at Endicott College...Also recruited by Air Force, Navy, and Army...Major is undecided.
